BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Chinese Media and Society
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20240201
DESCRIPTION:This course introduces students to contemporary Chinese media and entertainment industry, focusing on the development of Chinese media industry since 1978. The course will cover a range of Chinese media platforms including newspapers, film, radio, TV, online media channels, and social media. It will analyze specific cases to understand the dynamic relationship between society, media industry, culture, and media content in the globalized environment.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:News Group Project
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20240208
DESCRIPTION:Systematic analysis of American media coverage of China using content analysis and presenting findings through a PowerPoint presentation.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Film Individual Project
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20240226
DESCRIPTION:Students are required to choose one or two scenes from a film, analyze the relationship between story elements, language of film, and society, and submit a reaction paper.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:TV Individual Project
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20240322
DESCRIPTION:Details to be distributed in class for this project due on 3/22 at 10:00 pm.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Internet Group Project
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20240410
DESCRIPTION:Students need to analyze a media company or a particular time of a media company, identifying strengths, weaknesses, opportunities, and threats. Only a PowerPoint presentation is required.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Advertisement Individual Project
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20240428
DESCRIPTION:Students are to study how the U.S. and China advertise the same products in a one-page assignment. Details to be announced later for this project due on 4/28 at 10:00 pm.
END:VEVENT
